# Cursor Rules - Local-Only Operation

## Core Rules
- Work ONLY with local files - no cloud uploads
- Use local file system access exclusively
- No external indexing or cloud processing
- Respect privacy and keep all code analysis local

## Analysis Approach
- Read files directly using local file system
- Use grep, find, and other CLI tools for code search
- Analyze dependencies through package.json and imports
- Understand architecture through directory structure and README

## Forbidden Operations
- Do not upload any code to external servers
- Do not attempt cloud indexing
- Do not require internet connectivity for analysis
- Do not send code content to external APIs

## Project Context
This is Hydrabase - a P2P music metadata database built with TypeScript/Bun.

Key directories:
- /src/backend/ - Core P2P networking, database, API
- /src/frontend/ - Web UI 
- /src/types/ - TypeScript type definitions
- /test-data/ - Docker test configurations

Current development focus:
- UDP/TCP transport layer improvements
- WebSocket connection reliability  
- Peer discovery and authentication
- Docker containerization for testing

## Working Style
- Be direct and technical
- Focus on networking, P2P protocols, and distributed systems
- Prioritize code quality and test coverage
- Maintain backward compatibility